<HEADLINE>
Obama backs South Korea, slams 'irresponsible' North
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
TORONTO, Canada, June 26, 2010 (AFP)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
US President Barack Obama on Saturday said he stood "foursquare" behind South
Korean leader Lee Myung-Bak, as he scolded North Korea for its "irresponsible
behavior."
</P>
<P>
"We stand foursquare behind him," Obama said as he met with Lee, just after the
G8 leaders issued a tough statement condemning the alleged North Korean attack
that sank a South Korean warship in March.
</P>
<P>
Lee vowed Seoul "will react swiftly and strongly" to prevent another attack by
North Korea.
</P>
</TEXT>
