<HEADLINE>
Erdogan blasts Israel for 'bloody massacre' on aid ships
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Ankara, June 1, 2010 (AFP)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israel should be "punished" for its "bloody massacre" on aid ships bound for
Gaza, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Tuesday, as he warned the
Jewish state not to test Turkey's patience.
</P>
<P>
"The bloody massacre Israel carried out against ships carrying aid to Gaza
deserves condemnation," Erdogan told lawmakers from his ruling Justice and
Development Party, in an angry tirade against Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The insolent, irresponsible and impudent attack by Israel, which went against
law and trampled human honour underfoot, must definitely be punished," he
charged amid loud applause from his audience.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody should test Turkey's patience," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
